# Use orbctl for running commands

Always use the `orbctl run` prefix when running commands in this project.

## Examples

- Instead of: `cargo build`
  Use: `orbctl run cargo build`

- Instead of: `RUST_LOG=info cargo run`
  Use: `orbctl run RUST_LOG=info cargo run`

- Instead of: `cargo build && sudo ./target/debug/isolate-sandbox`
  Use: `orbctl run cargo build && orbctl run sudo ./target/debug/isolate-sandbox`

- Full example: `orbctl run RUST_LOG=info cargo build && orbctl run sudo RUST_LOG=info ./target/debug/isolate-sandbox`
